Package dev.blocky.library.jda.annotations

Root package of the JDA-Common annotations.

See: Description

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Deadline
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers that a method/class should be finish in the future.
    DeprecatedSince
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers since when a method/class is deprecated.
    ForRemoval
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers that a method/class should be removed in the future.
    ReplaceWith
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers, with which method/class a deprecated method/class should be replaced.
    Undocumented
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers that a method/class/constructor/package is not documented yet.

Package dev.blocky.library.jda.annotations Description

Root package of the JDA-Common annotations.
From here you can navigate to all annotations.
  • Deadline
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers that a method/class should be finish in the future.
  • Deprecated since
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers since when a method/class is deprecated.
  • For removal
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers that a method/class should be removed in the future.
  • Replace with
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers, with which method/class a deprecated method/class should be replaced.
  • Undocumented
    This is an annotation, which tells the developers that a method/class/constructor/package is not documented yet.
